    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Brice Turang** (73.59), **Mickey Moniak** (73.71), and **Austin Riley** (73.69) anchor our offensive strategy as our most efficient starts. **Brice Turang** earns a massive boost from his projected #2 spot in the order against the hittable arm of Jake Irvin, while **Austin Riley** benefits from an elite matchup against the high-xERA Jose Quintana, bolstered further by favorable park factors. **Mickey Moniak** is a standout value play today; despite his assumed #9 spot, his strong platoon advantage against Grant Holmes and a boost from park conditions make him an essential start. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** remains a critical piece for our category scarcity needs, maintaining a high floor (71.61) despite the headwind, as his ability to impact the scoreboard through multiple avenues justifies his start even in a tougher matchup against Rea.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Tyler Soderstrom** (52.39), who fell just shy of unseating **Dalton Rushing** (47.73) or **James Wood** (52.97). While **Tyler Soderstrom** offers strong potential, the optimizer ultimately favored **James Wood** due to his projected leadoff spot, which provides better opportunities for Runs, and **Dalton Rushing**'s stability in a matchup where the team expects to capitalize on Liberatore. Owners should remain vigilant regarding lineup volatility; because we are operating under \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions for players like **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Jose Caballero**, a late scratch in the order could significantly degrade their current efficiency scores. Furthermore, while **Seiya Suzuki** (59.22) is cleared for action, the \"Wind In\" advisory at his venue introduces a slight risk to his power output, though his steady baseline keeps him comfortably in the starting rotation.",
